---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CTA from "../components/CTA.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About Win-Win Apps"
  description="A small team building simple, affordable Shopify apps that help merchants and their customers."
  current="about"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Small team. Focused apps. Fair pricing.</h1>
      <p class="hero-lead">Win-Win Apps is an indie team building Shopify apps that do one job very well. We believe the best apps are the ones you install, set up in minutes, and stop thinking about.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container-narrow prose">
      <h2>What we build</h2>
      <p>We look for categories where two things are true: the leading apps leave obvious gaps in their reviews, and the job can be done with a lean stack. Most of the logic lives inside Shopify itself via theme app extensions and metafields. Our backend handles OAuth, admin UI, and bulk tools. That split keeps hosting costs low and storefronts fast.</p>

      <h2>How we work</h2>
      <p>We ship multiple apps per month using a disciplined process. Every app goes through the same stages: competitor research, build, test on real stores, and careful launch. We do not chase trends. We pick categories where we can charge less than everyone else and still make money because our overhead is low.</p>

      <h2>Who we are for</h2>
      <p>We build for Shopify merchants who want reliable, well-priced tools without the enterprise fluff. If you run a small or mid-size store and you are tired of apps that start at 29 dollars a month, you are our target customer.</p>

      <h2>Who is behind it</h2>
      <p>Win-Win Apps is built by Omar Shahban, a Shopify merchant of more than a decade, and Shane Stratton, a senior software engineer with experience at Amazon, IBM and Chess.com. Full bios are on the <a href="/team/">team page</a>.</p>

      <CTA
        heading="Get in touch"
        body="Merchant support, feedback and custom app ideas. The form reaches us directly."
        primaryLabel="Contact us"
        primaryHref="/contact/"
      />
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
